"Material Default" encompasses (though not exclusively) the happening of any one or a combination of the subsequent events:

1. A Party's persistent and significant failure to perform their contractual obligations under this Agreement, despite receiving proper notice and opportunity to remedy the situation;
2. The involuntary winding up or insolvency proceedings initiated against a Party;
3. A Party ceasing to conduct business activities without prior written notice to the other Party;
4. A material alteration in the scope of a Party's business as defined in this Agreement, made without obtaining the prior written consent of the other Party;
5. The unauthorized disclosure or use of Confidential Information by either Party for purposes not explicitly authorized under this Agreement.

Note that while this list is non-exhaustive, it serves to illustrate potential instances of Material Default. Other actions or circumstances that materially and adversely affect the performance of this Agreement may also constitute a Material Default.
